summary: This is an automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating that a final travel voucher (ID 11164814(1)) for an Epstein investigation witness interview trip to California has been approved by one approver and is pending further approval. The trip occurred in December 2019 and incurred $308.30 in expenses.

events.title: Epstein Investigation Witness Interview Trip
events.description: A trip was taken as part of the Epstein investigation for the purpose of conducting a witness interview in California.

keyFacts: A travel voucher for an Epstein investigation witness interview trip to California in December 2019 was approved in June 2020.
The trip was associated with case/project code R20NYS13444.
The total expenses for the voucher were $308.30 against an estimated trip cost of $574.30.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity related to the Epstein case as of late 2019.
The notification originates from the U.S. Department of Justice's internal travel management system (E2 Solutions).
